    "body": "Achually, this PR is not really about Zig, it is about replacing a Makefile, a shell script, a vimscript wrapper around the real vim-under-test with a simple NVIM-LUAAAAA wrapper\r\n\r\nAs it happens, we run a `--headless` nvim inside a `:terminal` layer, this is probably completely pointless.\r\nAlso there is still a lot remnants for oldesttests, but we don't have any except for test1.in which just checks the environment for following, non-exist-ant oldesttests. so just skip that!\r\n\r\nNow, the actuall vimscript code which runs in vim-under-test is _completely unchanged_ as for this PR. Although it would be tempting to poke into it to allow incremental output, that can be a separate, later thing to consider.\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n",
